author: @bhaveshsalvi4437
text: You were not right at (6:40)  loc and iloc difference . For ones who want to know - loc is label-based, which means that we have to specify the name of the rows and columns that we need to filter out  On the other hand, iloc is integer index-based. So here, we have to specify rows and columns by their integer index. Hope this clears out. Happy learning
